1 On page 1 of the printed bill, line 21, after “443.400” insert “, except that ‘residential facility’
2 does not include a secure residential treatment facility that is located on an Oregon State Hospital
3 campus or otherwise operated by the state”.
4 On page 4, delete lines 26 through 31 and insert:
5 “(2) For a behavioral health provider who is employed by an agency that contracts with a co-
6 ordinated care organization, the coordinated care organization shall reimburse the provider for the
7 cost of services provided to a member of the coordinated care organization retroactively to the date
8 that the provider submitted to the Oregon Health Authority an application for enrollment in the
9 state medical assistance program that resulted in the assignment of a provider identification
10 number.”.
